<br>
1) Cut them damn 100 page resolutions down!  Half the argument the Americans are putting forth is there is a stack of resolutions in the UN with no decent results. (remember that we Americans take information in 15-45 second commercials and anything else shuts us down)<br>
<br>
2) Organize your thoughts with a flow or structure that can be followed, and try not to write a post that covers more than one topic.<br>
<br>
3) Don't do that annoying thing where you pull the text out of someone else's post and then respond to it.  In legal writing we are taught that technique is one of the least persuasive forms of argument.  It says to the reader &quot;don't read this, it's not important&quot;.<br>
<br>
4) And finally, make short summaries at the beginning or ending or both so we can scan the argument to see if we want to invest our time in reading it.<br>
<br>
If you keep posts short and sweet, organized, un-bastardized, and summarized, we Americans will be more receptive.<br>
<br>
There is of course, the idea that you are just writing for your own therapy.  In that case... spam on.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bascension10244.showUserPublicProfile?gid=everas>Everas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>AD's Iksar Monk_0354</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#333333>(3/21/03 12:22:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fascension10244frm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1939.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: .</span><hr size=1> In other words try to appeal to those with little to no reading comprehension skill? Wow, well I suppose this is what happens when you belong to country with a relatively large population.<br>
